Intuition
The biker starts at altitude 0
Each gain[i] changes the altitude from point i to i+1
So the altitude at any point is just a running prefix sum
We need the maximum value among all these prefix sums (including 0)

Approach
Start with:

sum = 0 (current altitude)
ans = 0 (highest altitude so far)
For each value in gain:

Update current altitude: sum += gain[i]
Update maximum altitude using a branchless max technique
Global Max
Let diff = sum - ans

We want to add:

diff if diff > 0
0 otherwise
The sign of diff is extracted using:

(diff >> 31) → 0 if diff >= 0, -1 if diff < 0
Inverting this gives a mask:

~(diff >> 31) → -1 if diff >= 0, 0 if diff < 0
This mask selectively allows diff to be applied only when it is positive

The update keeps ans equal to the maximum of ans and sum

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n) Single pass through the array, constant work per element.

Space complexity:
O(1)
class Solution {
public:
    int largestAltitude(vector<int>& gain) {
        int n = gain.size();
        int mx = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            int alt = 0;

            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
                alt += gain[j];
            }

            mx = max(mx, alt);
        }

        return mx;
    }
};
